# Cursor legacy rules (fallback for older Cursor versions).
# Modern Cursor reads `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` — prefer those. This file restates the
# invariants so any Cursor version has them.

This is the Multilingual Smart Airport Wayfinding Assistant (Master IT 2026),
an agentic voice+text airport assistant (Arabic/Darija/French/English), case
study AUH.

Authoritative docs (read these; they are kept current):
- CLAUDE.md — full repo guide
- docs/PROGRESS.md — cross-session status board, decisions, session log (read at
  session start, update at end)
- docs/tdd/README.md + docs/tdd/TDD-0X-*.md — architecture and component contracts
- PROJECT_REQUIREMENTS.md — grading requirements

Non-negotiable invariants:
1. Owned/fine-tuned model, NOT just a hosted API. The graded ML contribution is
   the fine-tuned Whisper in asr_finetuning/ (Amassu/whisper-small-darija). LLM,
   TTS, and flight data (AirLabs) are external infrastructure by design.
2. Airport-agnostic — never hard-code airport facts; key data by airport_id
   (defaults to AUH).
3. Language is first-class — carry ar/ary/fr/en across boundaries; reply in the
   user's language; RTL for Arabic/Darija.
4. Flight/ticket number is a typed structured field, never parsed from audio.
5. Secrets server-side only — the AirLabs key lives in the backend; the frontend
   never calls AirLabs directly; never commit keys.

Consistency rule: propagate every change to ALL places that describe it (code,
config comments, module README, owning TDD, docs/PROGRESS.md, docs/tdd/README.md,
the PR description, CLAUDE.md, .cursor/rules, and AGENTS.md) in the same change.
grep for the old value before committing to prove no stale copy survives.

Git workflow: one branch + one PR per TDD/component, cut from an up-to-date main
(e.g. feat/tdd-02-agent). Small chores → chore/* or docs/* branch.
